               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus” (fols. 5ra-97vb)
 I-1)
                     Introduction (fols. 5ra-9va) 
 - On John the Evangelist as the author of
                     the book; on creation and the fall of the angel (fols. 5ra-7ra) 
 - Story
                     of the family of Adam (fols. 7ra-9va)
 I-2) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of
                     Jesus”: 71 miracles (fols. 9va-92va).
 I-3) Correspondence between King
                     Abgar and Jesus; the story of the martyrs of Akmim (fols. 92va-96va) (ed. S.
                     GRÉBAUT, “Les relations entre Abgar et Jésus”, ROC 21, 1918-19, 73-87; “La mort
                     des martyrs d'Akmim“, ibid. 92-93); a different version of correspondence
                     between King Abgar and Jesus (fols. 96va-97vb) (ed. GETATCHEW HAILE, "The
                     legend of Abgar in Ethiopic Tradition", OrChrP 55, 1989, 375-410, here
                     378-384)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The second part of Text I-1 is introduced with the word mǝʿrāf
                        “chapter”.</note>
                     <note>- The scribe included in numbering the miracles, the sections of Text
                        I-2.</note>
                     <note>- The miracles are introduced with words taʾammǝr “miracle”, nägär
                        “speech” or mǝʿrāf “chapter”. A few miracles have no particular introductory
                        word.</note>
                     <note>- The first part of Text I-3 is regarded as a part of Text I-2 (with the
                        title taʾammǝr "miracle" and with the number 72)</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
