                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: Walda Māryām. Walda Māryām
                        is mentioned as the scribe in the concluding supplication formula on <locus target="#97vb">97vb</locus>.
 His handwriting is similar to the
                        scribe Walda Māryām who produced Ms. QMB-005.<date>Late 19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits of sections of Text I-1;
                           numbers and incipits of miracles; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 A few groups of lines (alternating
                           with black lines) on the incipit page of Text I-1.</seg>
                     </handNote>
